@here what each file actually does explanation:
рџ“Ѓ Django App Files вЂ” What Each One Is For (Spottr)

Every feature (accounts, workouts, social, etc.) follows the same pattern.
Each file has one clear responsibility.

__init__.py

What it does

Marks the folder as a Python package

What goes in it

Usually nothing

Sometimes re-exports models for cleaner imports

Rule

No logic goes here

apps.py

What it does

Registers the app with Django

Controls how the app boots up

What goes in it

App name/config

(Rarely) startup hooks

Rule

No models, no business logic

admin.py

What it does

Registers models with Django Admin

What goes in it

Admin display configuration

Filters, search, read-only fields

Rule

Admin is a dev tool, not application logic

models.py (or models/)

What it does

Defines the database schema

What goes in it

Tables (models)

Fields & relationships

Constraints & indexes

Rule

Models describe data

Models do NOT perform actions

services.py

What it does

Holds all business logic

What goes in it

Multi-step workflows

Side effects (notifications, streak updates)

Cross-model logic

Rule

If something вЂњhappensвЂќ, it belongs here

migrations/

What it does

Tracks database schema changes over time

What goes in it

Auto-generated migration files only

Rule

DonвЂ™t manually edit unless you know why

How everything fits together

Request flow

API receives request

View calls a service

Service updates models + triggers side effects

Admin lets us inspect the data

Key principle

Views = HTTP
Services = business logic
Models = data
Admin = debugging